description: This file defines the main application routing component for a React-based frontend. It includes route definitions and placeholder components for different pages such as Swipe, Matches, Messages, Chat, Profile, and a 404 page. Each placeholder component uses common UI components like Card, Button, Modal, and Icon, to illustrate different UI states for the app's various sections.

methods.name: AppRouter()
methods.description: Main functional component that sets up the routing configuration for the application, mapping paths to placeholder components.

methods.name: SwipePlaceholder()
methods.description: Placeholder component for the swipe discovery page, featuring a Card with buttons and a modal explaining how discovery works.

methods.name: MatchesPlaceholder()
methods.description: Placeholder component for the matches page, with buttons to view matches and filters.

methods.name: MessagesPlaceholder()
methods.description: Placeholder component for the messages page, with buttons for new message and inbox settings.

methods.name: ChatPlaceholder()
methods.description: Placeholder component for an individual chat view, with a button for chat settings.

methods.name: ProfilePlaceholder()
methods.description: Placeholder component for user profile management, with buttons to edit profile and preview.

methods.name: NotFound()
methods.description: Component rendering a 404 Not Found message for unmatched routes.
